                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14295722" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 19:53:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;ve uncovered quite a big flaw - the subsetting code works on a per-page basis, which of course, breaks when you have more than one page. While named resources in PDF are per-page, the font objects that these resources point to are per-document. Whoops.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solutions is going to be rather involved - subsetting will need to be deferred until the document is about to be saved, and PDDocument will need to keep track of all fonts which are to be subset.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14295725" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 19:54:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, fonts will need to keep track of their own glyphs to be subset, rather than PDPageContentStream handing it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14295744" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 20:04:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue also encompasses &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2632&quot; title=&quot;Lost output when mixing subset and non-subset of the same font&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2632&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2632&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, in which the same font is embedded as both a subset and in full - which of course isn&apos;t possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14296299" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 02:47:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1655513 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1655513&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1655513&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2634&quot; title=&quot;Multiple text operations on multiple pages cause NPE in TTFSubsetter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2634&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2634&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Allow subset fonts to be used on more than one page&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14296302" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 02:49:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix was fairly complex, I had to move PDPageContentStream to the same package as PDDocument so that they can share a package-private API. The PDPageContentStream#setFont(PDFont, int, boolean) API has been removed and replaced with a new PDType0Font constructor which takes a boolean parameter controlling subsetting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14296609" author="tilman" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 09:01:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; Me thinks you had an accidental commit in PDFPrinter.java.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14296824" author="nev" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 13:20:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Many thanks and my respect. I&apos;ll try it out shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14297187" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 17:31:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1655760 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1655760&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1655760&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2634&quot; title=&quot;Multiple text operations on multiple pages cause NPE in TTFSubsetter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2634&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2634&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Revert accidental commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14297188" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 17:31:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well spotted - thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14297332" author="nev" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 18:51:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Perfect! Thank you )&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; I guess one small thing that people may bump into later is spaces: 00A0, 2008 and other spaces result in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: No glyph for U+2008 in font LiberationMono
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDCIDFontType2.encode(PDCIDFontType2.java:410)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDType0Font.encode(PDType0Font.java:284)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDFont.encode(PDFont.java:267)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I guess spaces are not part of the glyphs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14299177" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2015 20:20:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Spaces are regular glyphs. Your problem is that LiberationMono doesn&apos;t support those exotic spaces, e.g. Liberation Sans works just fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14299727" author="nev" created="Sat, 31 Jan 2015 09:30:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, stupid of me, varying width spaces in a mono font.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
